        "answer_count": 2,
        "title": "Unnecessarily long regex",
        "body": "<p>I have this string pattern I'm trying to match. It can contain some words enclosed within two curly braces. These curly braces have to be well-formed and they cannot be nested.<\/p>\n\n<p>For example:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>I have this {{example}} which is right\nHere {{is}} another {{example}} which is right\n{{ This {{ example }} is wrong }}\n{{ This }}example {{ is also { wrong }}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>I have constructed this regex which seems to work but it is very long and I think it can be simplified.<\/p>\n\n<p><code>\"^([^{}]*\\\\{\\\\{([^{}]*)\\\\}\\\\}[^{}]*)+$\"<\/code><\/p>\n\n<p>Is there any way I can simplify this?<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 38699926,
